edu.rit.util

Class AList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.AList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - List item data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class AList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Streamable
    Class AList provides a list of items stored in a dynamically-sized array.

    Operations take constant time unless otherwise specified. n is the number of items stored in the list.

      • position

        public int position(T i)
        Get the position of the given item in this list. This involves a linear scan of the list items starting from the beginning of the list; the returned value is the position of the first item encountered that is equal to the given item, as determined by the item's equals() method; if there is no such item, −1 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        i - Item.
        Returns:
        Position of matching item in the range 0 .. size()−1, or −1 if none.

      • position

        public int position(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Get the position of the first item in this list for which the given predicate is true. This involves a linear scan of the list items starting from the beginning of the list; the returned value is the position of the first item encountered for which the predicate's test() method returns true; if there is no such item, −1 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.
        Returns:
        Position of matching item in the range 0 .. size()−1, or −1 if none.

Time: O(n).
        Parameters:

      • forEachItemDo

        public void forEachItemDo(Action<T> action)
        Perform the given action on each item in this list. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given action's run() method is called, passing in the item. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the action adds items to or removes items from the list, the forEachItemDo() method's behavior is not specified.

        Parameters:
        action - Action.

      • forEachItemDo

        public <R> R forEachItemDo(ActionResult<T,R> action)
        Perform the given action on each item in this list and return a result. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given action's run() method is called, passing in the item. After all the list items have been processed, the given action's result() method is called, and its result is returned. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the action adds items to or removes items from the list, the forEachItemDo() method's behavior is not specified.

        Type Parameters:
        R - Result data type.
        Parameters:
        action - Action.
        Returns:
        Result of processing all the list items.

      • removeEachItemIf

        public void removeEachItemIf(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Evaluate the given predicate on, and possibly remove, each item in this list. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given predicate's test() method is called, passing in the item. If the test() method returns true, the item is removed from this list. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the predicate adds items to or removes items from the list, other than by returning true, the removeEachItemIf() method's behavior is not specified.

        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.

          int off,
          int len)
        Store this list's items in the given array. The first item is stored at index off, the second item at index off+1, and so on. The number of array elements set is len. If this list contains fewer than len items, the remaining array elements are set to null. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        array - Array in which to store items.
        off - Index at which to store first item.
        len - Number of items to store.
        Returns:
        The given array is returned.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if array is null.
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if off < 0, len < 0, or off+len > array.length.

      • searchUnsorted

        public int searchUnsorted(T a)
        Search this unordered list for the given item. The searchUnsorted() method calls the default searcher object's compare() method to compare items for equality only. The default searcher object is an instance of base class AList.Searcher. An O(n) linear search algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        Returns:
        If an item the same as a exists in this list, then the position of that item is returned. Otherwise, −1 is returned.

        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        searcher - Searcher object.
        Returns:
        If an item the same as a exists in this list, then the position of that item is returned. Otherwise, −1 is returned.

      • searchSorted

        public int searchSorted(T a)
        Search this ordered list for the given item. The searchSorted() method calls the default searcher object's compare() method to compare elements for equality and ordering. The default searcher object is an instance of base class AList.Searcher. It is assumed that this list is sorted in the order determined by the searcher's compare() method; otherwise, the searchSorted() method's behavior is not specified. An O(log n) binary search algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        Returns:
        If an item the same as a exists in this list, then the position of that item is returned. Otherwise, −1 is returned.

      • searchSorted

               AList.Searcher<T> searcher)
        Search this ordered list for the given item, using the given searcher. The searchSorted() method calls the searcher object's compare() method to compare elements for equality and ordering. It is assumed that this list is sorted in the order determined by the searcher's compare() method; otherwise, the searchSorted() method's behavior is not specified. An O(log n) binary search algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        searcher - Searcher object.
        Returns:
        If an item the same as a exists in this list, then the position of that item is returned. Otherwise, −1 is returned.

      • searchInterval

        public int searchInterval(T a)
        Search this ordered list for an interval containing the given item. The searchInterval() method calls the default searcher object's compare() method to compare elements for equality and ordering. The default searcher object is an instance of base class AList.Searcher. It is assumed that this list is sorted in the order determined by the searcher's compare() method; otherwise, the searchInterval() method's behavior is not specified. An O(log n) binary search algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        Returns:
        A position i such that get(i-1) ≤ a < get(i). If a < get(0), then i = 0 is returned. If get(size()-1) ≤ a, then i = size() is returned. If this list is empty, then i = −1 is returned.

      • searchInterval

        public int searchInterval(T a,
                 AList.Searcher<T> searcher)
        Search this ordered list for an interval containing the given item, using the given searcher. The searchInterval() method calls the searcher object's compare() method to compare elements for equality and ordering. It is assumed that this list is sorted in the order determined by the searcher's compare() method; otherwise, the searchInterval() method's behavior is not specified. An O(log n) binary search algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        a - Item to be searched for.
        searcher - Searcher object.
        Returns:
        A position i such that get(i-1) ≤ a < get(i). If a < get(0), then i = 0 is returned. If get(size()-1) ≤ a, then i = size() is returned. If this list is empty, then i = −1 is returned.

      • sort

        public void sort()
        Sort this list. The sort() method calls the default sorter object's comesBefore() method to determine the sorted order. The sort() method calls the default sorter object's swap() method to swap items during the sort. The default sorter object is an instance of base class AList.Sorter. An O(n log n) heapsort algorithm is used.

      • sort

        public void sort(AList.Sorter<T> sorter)
        Sort this list, using the given sorter. The sort() method calls the sorter object's comesBefore() method to determine the sorted order. The sort() method calls the sorter object's swap() method to swap items during the sort. An O(n log n) heapsort algorithm is used.
        Parameters:
        sorter - Sorter object.
